## TOPs Reality Capture Align Views

### Example HIP: 

* TOPs\_RealityCapture\_Align\_Views\_V001.hip

### Description:

Launch Reality Capture and create a new align views project file

The source photos and xmp metadata are loaded from:

* $HIP/images/\[\#\#\#\#\]/Reconstruction/Camera.NNNN.jpg  
* $HIP/images/\[\#\#\#\#\]/Reconstruction/Camera.NNNN.xmp

The region file is loaded from:

* $HIP\\metadata\\rec\_region.rcbox

The Reality Capture project file is saved to:

* $HIP/images/\[\#\#\#\#\]/project\_align.rcproj

![][image66]

#### Range Generate Node

Specify Range As: Value Range  
Value Range: 1-144 ("Right click \> Delete Channels" to unlock the number inputs)  
\[x\] Inclusive  
Store Value as: Custom Attribute  
Attribute Name: rangeValue  
\[x\] Set Range Attribute: range

Note: Set the "End Frame" range value to line up with the number of frames in the image sequence.  
![][image67]

##### **Strings:**

Name: frameInputFolder

Value: 500000
